laboratory_examinations.findings: This culture contains mixed bacterial types (>=3); any growth of P.aeruginosa, S.aureus, and beta hemolytic streptococci will be reported. If these bacteria are not reported, they are not present in this culture.

The common bile duct is mildly prominent, measuring 8 mm. There is a multiloculated, rim enhancing fluid collection in the right lower quadrant, the largest component measures 3.5 x 2.6 cm. An appendicolith is seen at the origin of the appendix, which is dilated measuring 9 mm.
